    {
      "name": "02 — Profile",
      "description": "Authenticated user profile, usage summary, and invoice history (JWT). Required to satisfy onboarding gating.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/me/profile",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "me",
                "profile"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Fetch the current user's profile."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "PUT /v1/me/profile",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"fullName\": \"Ada Lovelace\",\n  \"phone\": \"+1-415-555-0142\",\n  \"country\": \"US\",\n  \"timezone\": \"America/Los_Angeles\",\n  \"marketingOptIn\": true,\n  \"companyName\": \"Analytical Engines, Inc.\",\n  \"companySize\": \"11-50\",\n  \"industry\": \"Engineering\",\n  \"vatNumber\": \"US123456789\",\n  \"billingAddressLine1\": \"1 Babbage Way\",\n  \"billingAddressLine2\": \"Suite 1843\",\n  \"billingCity\": \"San Francisco\",\n  \"billingState\": \"CA\",\n  \"billingPostalCode\": \"94105\",\n  \"billingCountry\": \"US\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/me/profile",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "me",
                "profile"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Update profile. All fields are optional — see node/src/validators/profile.schema.ts for length and enum constraints."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/me/usage",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/me/usage",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "me",
                "usage"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns the current billing-period usage summary for the authenticated user.\n\nResponse shape:\n```json\n{\n  \"plan\": \"STARTER\",\n  \"planLabel\": \"Starter\",\n  \"limit\": 500,\n  \"used\": 42,\n  \"remaining\": 458,\n  \"overageCount\": 0,\n  \"periodStart\": \"2026-05-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"periodEnd\": \"2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"renewalDate\": \"2026-06-01T00:00:00.000Z\"\n}\n```\n`limit` and `remaining` are `null` for unlimited plans (e.g. ENTERPRISE). `renewalDate` is the active Stripe subscription's `currentPeriodEnd` when a subscription is present, otherwise the computed period end."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/me/invoices",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/me/invoices",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "me",
                "invoices"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns up to 100 billing invoices for the authenticated user, ordered by `periodStart` descending.\n\nResponse shape (array):\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"id\": \"inv_1234567890\",\n    \"number\": \"CAD-0001\",\n    \"status\": \"paid\",\n    \"amountPaid\": 2900,\n    \"currency\": \"usd\",\n    \"periodStart\": \"2026-04-01T00:00:00.000Z\",\n    \"hostedInvoiceUrl\": \"https://invoice.stripe.com/i/acct_xxx/inv_xxx\",\n    \"invoicePdf\": \"https://pay.stripe.com/invoice/acct_xxx/inv_xxx/pdf\"\n  }\n]\n```\n`amountPaid` is in the smallest currency unit (cents for USD). `hostedInvoiceUrl` and `invoicePdf` are `null` when not available (e.g. free-plan period with no charge)."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "03 — API Keys",
      "description": "Manage API keys (JWT). The plaintext `key` is returned only on creation — store it in `{{apiKey}}` (auto-saved by the test script).",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "GET /v1/keys",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/keys",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "keys"
              ]
            },
            "description": "List the caller's API keys (plaintext key never returned)."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/keys",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('apiKey', pm.response.json().key); pm.collectionVariables.set('keyId', pm.response.json().id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"local-dev\"\n}"
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/keys",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "keys"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Create a new API key. Response includes `id`, `name`, `keyPrefix`, `key` (plaintext, shown once), `createdAt`. The test script saves `key`→`{{apiKey}}` and `id`→`{{keyId}}`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "DELETE /v1/keys/:keyId",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{jwt}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/keys/:keyId",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "keys",
                ":keyId"
              ],
              "variable": [
                {
                  "key": "keyId",
                  "value": "{{keyId}}"
                }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Revoke an API key. Returns 204 on success."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "04 — Parse",
      "description": "Submit a CAD file (DWG, DXF, DWF, DGN, DWFx, or PDF) for parsing. Authenticated with the API key bearer token. Use `mode=async` (default) to return immediately with a `job_id`; use `mode=sync` to long-poll up to 60 s — responds 200 with the full result if the worker finishes in time, or 202 + `job_id` on timeout.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /v1/parse",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('jobId', pm.response.json().job_id);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "bearer",
              "bearer": [
                {
                  "key": "token",
                  "value": "{{apiKey}}",
                  "type": "string"
                }
              ]
            },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [],
            "body": {
              "mode": "formdata",
              "formdata": [
                {
                  "key": "file",
                  "type": "file",
                  "src": [],
                  "description": "Required. Supported formats: DWG, DXF, DWF, DGN, DWFx, PDF. Validated by magic bytes first, then extension."
                },
                {
                  "key": "webhookUrl",
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "",
                  "description": "Optional. Must be a valid URL — receives a POST when the job completes."
                },
                {
                  "key": "mode",
                  "type": "text",
                  "value": "async",
                  "description": "Optional. `async` (default) — returns 202 + job_id immediately. `sync` — long-polls up to 60 s; returns 200 with full result body if the worker finishes in time, otherwise 202 + job_id."
                }
              ]
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{baseUrl}}/v1/parse",
              "host": [
                "{{baseUrl}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "v1",
                "parse"
              ]
            },
