      "name": "06 — Billing",
      "description": "Stripe-backed billing. The webhook entry is reference-only — Stripe is the real caller and signs requests with `Stripe-Signature`.\n\n**CADLens job webhook** (sent to the customer's `webhookUrl` on job completion):\n```json\n{\n  \"eventId\": \"<uuid>\",\n  \"sequence\": 1,\n  \"event\": \"job.completed\",\n  \"jobId\": \"<uuid>\",\n  \"status\": \"COMPLETED\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-15T12:00:00.000Z\",\n  \"result\": {\n    \"entityCount\": 142,\n    \"layerCount\": 8,\n    \"imageUrl\": \"https://s3…/preview.png?X-Amz-Expires=86400\",\n    \"vectorJson\": [ /* parsed entities array — inline */ ],\n    \"layersJson\": [ /* layer metadata — inline */ ],\n    \"metadata\": { /* drawing metadata — inline */ }\n  }\n}\n```\nNote: `resultUrl` (formerly a signed S3 URL to vector.json) has been removed. The vector data, layer metadata, and drawing metadata are now delivered inline in `vectorJson`, `layersJson`, and `metadata` respectively. `imageUrl` is a presigned S3 URL with a 24-hour TTL.",
